******
Europe
---
[1] Latvia
Date: Fri 5 Jan 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/latvia-reports-first-measles-cases-since-2014/


For the 1st time in 3 years, Latvia has reported confirmed measles cases, according to a Delfi report (computer translated).

The Center for Disease Prevention and Control (SPKC) reports 4 cases of measles infection among adults have been laboratory confirmed. All the patients are hospitalized for their illness.

The report doesn't state ages or vaccination status of the ill patients.

Given the worsening situation, the SPKC encourages family doctors and hospitals to pay attention to specific measles prevention and vaccination.

--
